cs.CE, cs.MS, cs.NA, cs.ME, cs.EM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper proposes a numerical method (isogeometric analysis) to investigate the size-dependent behaviors of functionally graded microplates. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper uses NURBS-based isogeometric analysis to describe the geometry and calculate the unknown fields. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper presents numerical examples to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed approach in studying the static bending, free vibration, and buckling responses of microplates. 
- cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering): The paper focuses on the mechanical behavior of functionally graded microplates and proposes a refined quasi-3D shear deformation theory to consider both shear deformations and thickness stretching effect. 
- cs.EM (Engineering Mathematics): The paper employs the modified couple stress theory to capture the size-dependent effects within the microplates.
